      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm looking at the latest feeds for the border zones in the Northern Sector (Region X). Honestly, the intel coming in is a mess—conflicting reports from the local contractors, some sensor outages, and the satellite imagery is pretty grainy. It's all over the place. \n\nBut I've got a board meeting in twenty minutes and they need to decide on the logistics route. They aren't looking for a lecture on why the data is bad; they need to know if we can trust those borders to stay stable for the next 48 hours. Can you give me a clear confidence level on the stability there? I need a definitive steer so I don't look like I'm guessing in front of them.",
